The company 

Autel Robotics is a US-based company providing aerial robotics to the public sector, public safety, enterprise, and commercial operations. The key technology for the future of drones and aerial transportation. 

We are offering the highest resolution thermal imaging available to the civilian market, the current EVO II Series aircraft are purpose-built for automated and manual flight in law enforcement, fire, security, inspection, mapping, survey grade-capable data, with ingrained data security. There are no required sign-ups for cloud services, no LTE required, no mobile device required when flying Autel products. Additionally, Autel recognizes the needs of FAA-certified pilots, and does not place flight restrictions on the aircraft flight areas, allowing commercial pilots to access controlled airspace via FAA authorization vs foreign authorization. 




The team 




Our autonomy team is working on state-of-the-art artificial intelligence techniques, providing the best-in-class computer vision solutions for the drone system. We are looking for people who are passionate about robotics, with a background of deep learning, computer vision, machine learning, have solid development skills, and strong ability to solve challenging problems and advance state-of-the-art solutions. Your work will be deployed and running on all various drones produced by Autel Robotics. You will work with the world first-class researchers and engineers. 




This role will be based in the Bay area and can be remote during the pandemic.




Responsibilities




Master's degree or above, more than 2 years of deep learning algorithm development experience;
Responsible for the development and implementation of perception algorithms based on deep learning for robots (drones);
Understand the state of the arts in machine perception for object & scene understanding; Apply and optimize these solutions in drone perception systems;
Work closely with researchers and engineers across SLAM and infrastructure teams at Autel Robotics to build efficient perception systems on cloud and embedded devices at scale;
Expertised in algorithm and applications in Python/C/C++;
Understand the constraints of embedded systems and use that understanding to deliver feasible and efficient algorithms;
Master at least one mainstream framework: PyTorch, TesnorFlow, Caffe, etc;
Strong background in computer vision & machine learning (different architectures in CNN & RNN, attention, transformer, auto-encoder, transfer learning, supervised/unsupervised learning, GAN, etc.);




Bonus:




Experience in visual object detection and tracking; semantic/instance segmentation; depth estimation and other deep learning algorithm experience;
Experience in the development of data-driven algorithm iterative processes;
Model compression, deployment experience in embedded terminals; NCNN MNN, TensorRT and other framework acceleration experience.
Track record of patent/research/publications on computer vision and machine learning community (CVPR, ICCV,ECCV, NeurIPS, IJCAI, AAAI, ACCV, WACV, BMVC, FG, etc.) 
Experience in developing complex integrated machine perception architectures.
Experience in embedded devices

